{"questionId":"19712","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The time, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> minutes, taken to complete a jigsaw puzzle can be modelled by a normal&nbsp;distribution with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math> and standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>It is found that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;of times taken to complete the jigsaw puzzle are longer than&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>36</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;minutes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>29</mn></math> in the remainder of the question.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Six randomly chosen people complete the jigsaw puzzle.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Having spent <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn></math> minutes attempting the jigsaw puzzle, a randomly chosen person had not&nbsp;yet completed the puzzle.</p>\n<p>Find the probability that this person will take more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math> minutes to complete the&nbsp;jigsaw puzzle.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizes that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>25</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is required&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong>M1</strong> for recognizing conditional probability.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>∩</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>(A1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>30</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6049</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8016</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>M1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>755</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[4</strong><strong>&nbsp;marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19712","referenceCode":"EXN.2.SL.TZ0.8e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Having spent 25 minutes attempting the jigsaw puzzle, a randomly chosen person had not yet completed the puzzle. Find the probability that this person will take more than 30 minute","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Conditional and independent probabilities, test for independence"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}